: <ul><li>$P(X&le;g | &mu;=$mean ; &sigma;=$sigma)=$[$kans/100]</li><li>Look up in your probability chart, the probability nearest to $[$kans/100] </li><li>That should be $kans1</li><li>The z_value fot this is:  z=$Z1</li><li>Use the formula z=(g - &mu; )/ &sigma; </li><li>So $Z1=(g-$mean)/$sigma</li><li>Thus $Z1*$sigma=g-$mean</li><li>And $[$Z1*$sigma]=g-$mean</li><li>So g=$(answer$n)</li></ul>
