: <ul><li>$P($g1 &le; V &lt; g<b>&nbsp;|&nbsp;</b> &mu; = $mean and &sigma; = $sigma) = $kans</li><li>Determine $P(V &lt; $g1<b>&nbsp;|&nbsp;</b> &mu; = $mean and &sigma; = $sigma)</li><li>$P(V &lt; $g1<b>&nbsp;|&nbsp;</b> &mu; = $mean and &sigma; = $sigma) = $K</li><li>$P(V &lt; g<b>&nbsp;|&nbsp;</b> &mu; = $mean and &sigma; = $sigma) = $K + $kans &asymp; $[$K+$kans]</li><li>input for  a TexasInstruments Ti83 &trade; graphical calculator <kbd>invNorm</kbd>($[($K+$kans)],$mean,$sigma)</li><li>So g=$g2 </li></ul>
