: <ul><li>$P(V &ge; $g<b>&nbsp;|&nbsp;</b> &mu; = $mean and &sigma; = <b>?</b> ) = $[1-$kans]</li><li>$P(V &lt; $g<b>&nbsp;|&nbsp;</b> &mu; = $mean and &sigma; = <b>?</b> ) = $kans</li><li>input for  a TexasInstruments Ti83 &trade; graphical calculator <kbd>invNorm</kbd>($kans) ; this will bring you the z-value</li><li>&sigma; = ($g - &mu;)/z</li><li>&sigma; = ($g - $mean)/$Z</li><li>So the standard deviation is $sigma</li></ul>
